{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6eebf290-d06c-40d2-98b0-c7f6260ab664","content":"Could you clarify what you mean by \"file system wrapper\"? `System.IO.Abstractions` already provides:\n\n- **`FileSystem`** — the real implementation of `IFileSystem`\n- **`MockFileSystem`** — an in-memory fake for testing\n\nAre you looking for one of these?\n\n1. A **decorator** around `IFileSystem` that adds logging, caching, or similar cross-cutting concerns?\n2. A **custom in-memory implementation** for testing (beyond `MockFileSystem`)?\n3. A **DI registration helper** that wires up `FileSystem` as `IFileSystem`?\n4. Something else entirely?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17c48087-42af-4a5d-90b8-df17fc41fa2c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a simple codebase that uses `System.IO.Abstractions`'s `IFileSystem` interface. They want me to generate a file system wrapper. \n\nBut wait - `System.IO.Abstractions` already provides `IFileSystem` and a default implementation `FileSystem`. So what kind of wrapper do they want?\n\nTypically when people say \"file system wrapper\" in the context of `System.IO.Abstractions`, they might mean:\n1. A custom wrapper/decorator around `IFileSystem` that adds logging, caching, or other cross-cutting concerns\n2. A simple wrapper class that wraps the real `System.IO.Abstractions.FileSystem` for DI registration\n\n\n3. An in-memory implementation for testing\n\nThe request is a bit ambiguous though. They mention their code already uses `IFileSystem` everywhere and they want a wrapper generated, but `System.IO.Abstractions` already provides the real implementation. I'm wondering if they're looking for a decorator pattern wrapper that adds functionality on top, or if they just need help setting up the abstraction properly.\n\nI should probably ask what specific behavior they want from this wrapper since \"file system wrapper\" could mean several different things in this context.","outputTokens":593,"requestId":"1BD